1 A HOUSE RESOLUTION honoring the Food Bank of
2 Northwest Indiana for its service and dedication to the
3 communities and families of Northwest Indiana.
4 Whereas, Under the visionary leadership of Victor Garcia,
5 President and Chief Executive Officer of the Food Bank of
6 Northwest Indiana, the organization has expanded its capacity,
7 strengthened community partnerships, and advanced innovative
8 strategies to combat hunger while ensuring operational
9 excellence, accountability, and compassionate service;
10 Whereas, The Food Bank operates a 72,000-square-foot
11 facility in Merrillville, staffed by 34 dedicated employees, and
12 is equipped with custom-built cold storage and a fleet of
13 refrigerated trucks and vans that ensure the safe collection and
14 distribution of donated food;
20262344
HR 1510/DI 140 2026

2
1 Whereas, In 2025, the Food Bank of Northwest Indiana
2 distributed more than 11 million pounds of food, serving an
3 average of over 60,000 individuals each month through a
4 strong network of over 150 partner non-profits, food pantries,
5 congregate meal sites, and soup kitchens;
6 Whereas, The Food Bank delivers critical direct service
7 programs, including Mobile Market, The Emergency Food
8 Assistance Program (TEFAP), the Commodity Supplemental
9 Food Program (CSFP) that provides home-delivered groceries
10 to 1,700 seniors monthly, Food is Medicine initiatives in
11 partnership with health care providers, Operation Full Pack to
12 serve veterans, and Homeless Street Outreach in the city of
13 Gary;
14 Whereas, The Food Bank of Northwest Indiana is a
15 recognized leader in innovation and access, and among the first
16 organizations in the nation to successfully launch automated
17 refrigerated smart lockers for charitable food distribution, and
18 was inducted into the Purdue Northwest Society of Innovators
19 in 2024; and
20 Whereas, Through SNAP Outreach services and workforce
21 partnerships with WorkOne to provide job training and
22 certifications in warehousing and logistics, the Food Bank
23 addresses both immediate hunger and long term economic
24 stability under the leadership of Tricia Sheaks, Vice President
25 of Operations and Community Impact: Therefore,
26 Be it resolved by the House of Representatives of the
27 General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
28 SECTION 1. That the Indiana House of Representatives
29 honors the Food Bank of Northwest Indiana for its
30 extraordinary service, innovation, and dedication to improving
31 the health and well-being of the communities it serves and
32 expresses deep gratitude for its lasting impact.
33 SECTION 2. That the Principal Clerk of the House of
34 Representatives shall transmit copies of this resolution to State
35 Representative Mike Andrade for distribution.
